data.name: Chicken and Rice Soup
data.quickTastyDescription: A comforting and hearty soup, perfect for any day of the week.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add diced onion, carrots, and celery. Saut√© until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add minced garlic and cook for an additional minute until fragrant.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Stir in the chicken breast and rice. Reduce heat to a simmer.
Cook for 20 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the rice is tender.
Remove the chicken, shred it with two forks, and return it to the pot.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with parsley before serving.
